The paper deals with lower bounds for geometric problems, which are typically studied in the computational geometry community (cs.CG). The use of the exponent $1-1/d$ suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.CC), as this is a common technique for analyzing the running time of such problems. The paper also discusses Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs), which are a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CE).
